// @test regression/INV001-ternary-cross-type-branches
// @description Cross-type ternary branches yield nonsense values (e.g. int|color, string|float). We flag them as errors using TV's CE10123 operator diagnostic form. See investigations/INV001-ternary-branch-compat/notes.md.
// @expects parse: success
// @expects error: line=4, message=/Cannot call "operator \?:"/
// @expects error: line=5, message=/Cannot call "operator \?:"/
// @expects error: line=6, message=/Cannot call "operator \?:"/
//@version=6
indicator("INV001 - cross-type ternary branches")
cond = close > open
a = cond ? 1 : color.red
b = cond ? "hello" : 3.14
c = cond ? color.green : "label"
plot(close)
